        <div class="msgSubject">Tanks at the end of Wrath or pre-Cata not sure which I mean.</div>
        <div class="sm notbold">
          
          Posted: 2010-10-01 05:09:34   | <input type="checkbox" name="quote-1285931374201045013" id="quote-1285931374201045013" class="msgQuoteCheck"/><label for="quote-1285931374201045013"> Quote</label>  | <a href="/forum.html?forum=21&amp;mid=1285931374201045013&amp;post=1&amp;replyto=1285931374201045013&amp;page=1" class="icon-replytothis" rel="nofollow" onclick="return multiQuote(this)">Reply to Post</a> | <a id="FOLLOW_MID_1285931374201045013" onclick="followToggle('add','1285931374201045013')" href="javascript:" class="icon-follow">Follow</a> 
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgWhoFrame">
        <div class="msgUM"><a class="msgWhoName Guru" href="/users/Horsemouth">Horsemouth</a><div class="msgWhoTitle Guru">Guru</div></div><div class="msgAvatar"></div><div class="msgStar"><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/></div><div class="msgWhoNum">4,402 posts</div>
        <div class="msgScore">
          Score: Good  
          <div class="msgRatings"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">So I leveled a <a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Boulderfist&amp;cn=Lehua" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Boulderfist&amp;cn=Lehua">horde DK tank</a> recently as something to do as the xpac winds down. <br /> <br />I hit 80 earlier today so of course hit heroics. I had been farming regular instances with LFD and had around low 20k HP ~30% avoidance and over 540 defense the second I hit 80, this is with out any BoE gear or any help from my other toons as he is on a different server. Since my stats are more than enough for heroics I felt this would be fine. <br /> <br />Mostly it was, only had one group get angry and boot me from H HoS, this was after I somehow managed to OT Ignis for the weekly thus making it funnier. The rest either said nothing or laughed and said something to the effect of you have to start somewhere. <br /> <br />My post is about the angry folks or the have to start somewhere people. I had all but 1 or 2 pieces from Occy and CoS but otherwise the cream of the regular instance crop of gear. People would have been excited to have me tank when the xpac dropped. I have a geared tank on my main server that could do three heroics in the time it this guy to do one. Both get the job done, just one has more gear and a spammable AoE attack. <br /> <br />Do tanks these days have to do ToC and the ICC 5 mans to gear up for heroics these days? They shouldn't as those places drop better gear than heroics. Gearing up in instances that drop better gear than heroics to do heroics is a retarded concept. Yet is that now the case? <br /> <br />I mean when I do randoms on my healer, also geared, I don't care what the tank has for gear. I could heal a mage through most heroics if they wanted to tank and most of the healers I have encountered are similarly geared.  <br /> <br />So heals aren't the issue. As they are either geared so it is irrelevant or don't mind as I can't really chain pull or anything so they don't have issues.  <br /> <br />The issue seems to be DPS as the healers have never complained. They seem to have been spoiled by Wrath, well the last half of Wrath as it was a whole different ball game the first year or so. DPS are too often very impatient, cocky and arrogant, whether outright or in a backhanded sort of way. <br /> <br />The thing that worries me is when the pre-Cata changes hit what will happen? Tanks wont be AoE machines even with gear as tank AoE is getting nerfed, TO THE GROUND BABY, yet most DPS wont slow down or CC. Healers will not be in infinite mana mode. Maybe tanks and heals wont be as affected at level 80 but I'm sure there will be a noticeable shift in how heroics are run, raids as well. <br /> <br />As the new class changes are upon us what do you folks think will end up being different in that magical, awkward and bizarre time that is the post Wrath pre Cata period of time? <br /> <br />/ramble <div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><span class="sm">Cataclysm will destroy your class and make it be terrible. The previews obviously make it seem that way and your worst fears, preconceived notions and speculations based on current mechanics are true. So bunker down and fear. Fear the future, it will be horrendous.</span> <br /> <br /><a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Destromath&amp;cn=Kanilehua" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Destromath&amp;cn=Kanilehua">priest</a> <a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Destromath&amp;cn=Makapuu" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Destromath&amp;cn=Makapuu">bear</a> <br /> <br />Diligently learning about 4.0.1 as we speak.</div></div>
