      <div class="msgContentFrame">Most DPS are lazy tards: Most tanks are slow tards.  (Spoken from the perspective of a DPS.) <br /> <br />They don't want to wait till you have threat: A good tank that knows what they're doing will have enough threat from one move to get a sufficient head start even on the most earnest and fast-hitting DPS.  Piss-poor tanks like Paladins who only drop consecration (which takes a tick or two to get threat) instead of swinging will not maintain aggro.  That's the tank's fault, not the DPS. (Spoken from the perspective of a tank.) <br /> <br />Tanks and Healers have a bond: Then why do so many tanks not listen to the healer?  (Spoken from the healer's POV.) <br /> <br /> <br />There are many bad qualities for many different types of characters.  They all have their high points and low points.  When you get a group together that encompasses all the high points, it's a beautiful thing.  One bad apple will ruin it...and it's NOT always gonna be the DPS.</div>
