      <div class="msgContentFrame">My philosophy is to play to the level of the group. It's a team, even if it's a random pug. Personal performance (i.e. topping the meter) means nothing. Team success = win. <br /> <br />As DPS my job is to <b>do as much damage as threat allows</b> and help the team kill the bosses. That's it. Easiest job in the game. <br /> <br />As a tank my job is keep the healer alive. DPS dying to fire or threat are on their own. It's not like tanks have a button that's ZOMG THREAT BEAST that we're not using &quot;just in case&quot;. Tanks have a set of standard abilities that produce a relatively steady stream of threat. Aside from taunts, a competent tank will output a basic mean-average of threat per second. Hitting buttons harder don't give additional threat, sadly. <br /> <br />Players, even very progressed ones, need to remember that they are playing a co-operative game. Period.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><span class="sm">&quot;I'm gonna need to see more math I don't understand to believe all this&quot; <br />日本人彼女募集中 <br /><a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Proudmoore&amp;n=Zede" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Proudmoore&amp;n=Zede">Zede the Undying</a> • <a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Proudmoore&amp;n=Phezz" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Proudmoore&amp;n=Phezz">Phezz, the Insane Kingslayer</a> • <a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Proudmoore&amp;n=Dehlia" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Proudmoore&amp;n=Dehlia">Dehlia the Love Fool</a></span></div></div>
