      <div class="msgContentFrame">Having two DPS(rogue/mage), and a tank/healer(prot/holy pally) that all do ICC, I'll tell you this: <br /> <br />Most DPS are lazy.as.hell. <br /> <br />Keep in mind, my main is a rogue, the tank is my alt. Also, there might be reasons your tank is slow. Unlike you, the tank has to control the rate of flow through the heroic for the ENTIRE group. He has to tank, pull, watch healers mana, watch for DPS to pull aggro or break CC. If the healer is low, he stops etc. Or he may actually be new to 80 and/or tanking. I had to learn to tank 5 mans all by myself when I first hit 80, and being undergeared, I just told people I was learning and to please bear with me. 99% of groups were fine with it, tanks are held in higher esteem than other roles from what I've noticed. Again, this is from playing DPS and Tanking all the way from regular 5 mans through ICC. Most players don't understand tanking, and to be honest, it scares them, it scared the hell out of me for oh I dunno, about 8 years now? <br /> <br />I love my tank, to be honest, I like playing him more than my DPS classes, but no matter how much fun I'm having, it's still stressful. <br /> <br /> <br />I am not worried about group dynamics in cata, we adjusted from vanilla to TBC, and then TBC into wrath. Now, you may argue about idiot players all day, but the end result is, I can safely pug every heroic in wrath and be successful, so this mens we adjusted. <br /> <br />We will again as a playerbase as soon as Cata comes around. The good players will learn, the bads will still be bad and shunned.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Oderint dum metuant <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Mistress Darqflame wrote:</div><div class="orig">Filter is a zamgod!</div></div> <br /></div></div>
