      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Kavekk the Ludicrous wrote:</div><div class="orig">Having tried both (mage, rogue, prot/ret paladin, feral druid) I don't really think tanking is harder than DPSing, and if people hold it in awe (I suspect they just don't want to piss tanks off as they're rarer) it's probably out of ignorance. I dunno, I think you're projecting, but it's perfectly possible that it's me that's incorrect in assuming most people feel the way I do about it; I've never felt intimidated by tanking.</div></div> <br /> <br />I remember between 68 and 70 with this toon I couldn't tank the NR instances, mainly do to gear availability issues. So I would just DPS with what little DPS gear I had and my tank spec.  <br /> <br />Had one tank who obviously had been tanking for a while. Just the way he would move around, positions mobs and all the other little things that make a good tank. I said something to him to the effect that I knew he had a main that was a tank. <br /> <br />He was startled at first and I told him it was obvious he had been tanking for a long time. I was right. <br /> <br />Also had a bunch of tanks, most of them to be honest, that you could tell they weren't used to tanking.  <br /> <br />All of the things DPS have to do, with the exception of CC, a tank also has to do but tanks have to do more. That is why people don't want to tank and many fail or don't excel at it in general. That and a tank not doing the little things that most DPS don't typically pick up on will be noticed. Depending on the content and persons involved how much this matters can vary greatly.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><span class="sm">Cataclysm will destroy your class and make it be terrible. The previews obviously make it seem that way and your worst fears, preconceived notions and speculations based on current mechanics are true. So bunker down and fear. Fear the future, it 