ling everyone to &quot;Run Away!&quot; I'm sitting there DPSing and popping a health pot (Recuperate post-4.0) and healers are freaking out for nothing. <br /> <br />The &quot;experienced tank/DPS/healer is obvious&quot; argument is pretty easy to make; we've all run into just average DPS, healers, and tanks who make us go &quot;meh, he's decent but could do this this and this&quot; to be better. <br /> <br />I'm with Kavekk, tanking/healing isn't necessarily harder once you have a handle on your abilities. At least if you've played a melee class, you should know how to position mobs, and once you have your abilities set, it shouldn't be that hard to tank.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><span class="sm"><a href="HTTP://dictionary.reference.com/browse/theophany" rel="external nofollow" title="dictionary.reference.com/browse/theophany"><b>The·oph·a·ny</b></a> <i>(thē-ŏf'ə-nē)</i> <br />An appearance of a god to a human; a divine manifestation. <br /> <br /><a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Draka&amp;cn=Korz" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Draka&amp;cn=Korz">Rogue</a> | <a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?cn=K%C3%B5rz&amp;r=Draka" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?cn=Kõrz&amp;r=Draka">Shaman</a> | <a href="/forum.html?forum=214&amp;mid=1284152030146222020" rel="external" title="wow.allakhazam.com/forum.html?forum=214&amp;mid=1284152030146222020">PvP 101</a></span></div></div>
