      <div class="msgContentFrame">I have a bunch of toons (almost embarrassed to admit how many 80's). I've done plenty of dpsing, healing, and tanking. Imho, that's the order of difficulty. <br /> <br />Dps is pretty easy. It's harder to do it well, but it's still not that hard. <br /> <br />Healing is usually pretty easy, but it can be tricky sometimes. If the tank is undergeared or you are barely high enough level and tend to run out of mana, or if there is some terrible situation with an unexpected pat or something, well, it can get hairy. Most of the time it's not bad, though. If the group is overgeared (WoLK heroics in the past year or so), you can practically snooze through it. 11121112111... snore... <br /> <br />Tanking isn't always hard. If the healer is good and the dps aren't stupid, it can be pretty smooth. If the dps run amok AOE-ing every group of mobs the escond they see it, or if the healer is kinda ADD, or if someone's pet does something crazy, it can be very difficult. And you always have to know the route to take, and where the pats are, and you have to keep an eye on threat, etc etc. Even an easy run takes a certain amount of effort and attention. <br /> <br />That's just my two scents. <br /> <br />;-) </div>
