      <div class="msgContentFrame">With Respect to the tanks needing crazy gear to do the most basic stuff - Yes.  People are horribly lazy and don't want challenge.  Generally this is the DPS - As you point out. <br /> <br />This stems from two sources.  First - The DPS are generally the easiest played classes - thus if jack-assery is to be found - it's often found among their ranks.  Second - The DPS are forced to wait for 20+ minutes for a run - thus they are generally frustrated and annoyed to begin with.  So the moment they sense a weak tank or healer (or occasionally fellow DPS) - they turn on them.  Hey - they took 20 minutes to wait and now they want/demand success. <br /> <br />With respect to the lack of CC or whatever...  Well, it's generally not needed in Wrath and thus they have been spoiled.  I remember when my main job was to Sheep.  From the tank back in Shattered Halls:  &quot;Lock and Rogue, do you're thing, but Mage - I don't care what you do - so long as 'Moon' stays sheeped until I break it.&quot;  Back then a good mage knew how to reapply sheep.  I honestly do not recall the last time I used the spell.  Really - I'm not joking.  It used to be &quot;=&quot; on my keybindings because it was out of the way, but easily found and I used it often.  I unbound it a few months ago.   <br /> <br />As to your point about 'instant' or 'snap-on' AOE agro....  Perhaps it's a good thing.  Perhaps holding the attention of an entire instance isn't helping the game.  Will it be tougher to Paly tank - Yeah, I guess.  But maybe if we can get the damn DPS to CC - we can find a happy medium between Wrath (AOE) and TBC (Shattered Halls)...<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Most things you worry about never happen anyway.</div></div>
