      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Borsuk wrote:</div><div class="orig">As to your point about 'instant' or 'snap-on' AOE agro.... Perhaps it's a good thing. Perhaps holding the attention of an entire instance isn't helping the game. Will it be tougher to Paly tank - Yeah, I guess. But maybe if we can get the damn DPS to CC - we can find a happy medium between Wrath (AOE) and TBC (Shattered Halls)...</div></div> <br />It was a point of pride for me that I was able to tank Shattered Halls as a warrior in TBC with one rogue for CC (in a <i>good</i> group, but still). And while I don't think that instances need to go back to that level of craziness, the AoE zergfest that was WotLK got boring really quickly. It'd be nice to see some skill and finesse on the part of the whole group required again to complete instances without wiping. Does this mean that LFG will be a terrible place for a while? Possibly. But in the long run, it'll be good for the game overall.</div>
