      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">This stems from two sources. First - The DPS are generally the easiest played classes - thus if jack-assery is to be found - it's often found among their ranks. Second - The DPS are forced to wait for 20+ minutes for a run - thus they are generally frustrated and annoyed to begin with. So the moment they sense a weak tank or healer (or occasionally fellow DPS) - they turn on them. Hey - they took 20 minutes to wait and now they want/demand success. </div></div> <br /> <br />I don't think DPS are the easiest classes to play.  <br /> <br />What I see is that we are used to having the tank and the healer make up for all the faults on DPSers. So that <u>we leave DPSers nothing to care about other than the amount of damage that they do</u>. <br /> <br />1. DPS has to keep themselves alive by avoiding aggro and other sources of avoidable damage, and when needed, they have to use defensive cooldowns to avoid the aggro or mitigate damage. <br /> <br />2. DPS has to measure the mobs in contrast to the group, determine which are most threatning so that they counter them and prioritize properly. For most heroics it's 100% about doing AoE spam, but when it isn't, it isn't. <br /> <br />3. DPS has to do interrupts and balance the trade-off of spending an interrupt to avoid a large amount of incoming damage or to prevent a healing move from restoring massive amounts of enemy HP. <br /> <br />4. They also have manage their various miscelaneous abilities that significantly help groups by reducing the effort required or improving the effect of their abilities. <br /> <br />Instead, we get DPS pulling aggro, getting killed from it without ever using any of their defensive cooldowns and it's the tank that needs to &quot;learn2taunt&quot; and the healer that needs to &quot;learn2heal&quot;. <br /> <br />And this has a huge impact on tanks, the reason is, the DPSers that tend to take too much avoidable damage burden healers, sometimes (mostly on bosses that like to draw circles on the floor) they can burden healers to a point that they can't keep up the heals and the tank dies. Trust me, tanks are very easy to keep up when the DPS don't overburden healers. <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct  5th 2010  2:35am by xorq </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>NOTE: I may post comments about my like/dislike/approval/disapproval of game features. <br />1- They are NOT a complaint. They are a perspective. <br />2- They are NOT advocacy. They are a perspective.</div></div>
