      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">...speaking purely on the roll of DPS in Heroics... <br /> <br />If DPS isn't the easiest job - what is? </div></div> <br /> <br /> <br />Yes, DPS can perform poorly and still get by.  That just means it's easiest to eek by in the current environment as a DPS.  It doesn't mean performing well as a DPS is the easiest &quot;job&quot;. <br /> <br />Looking at the difficulty of heroics at a time when everyone overgears the content is kind of pointless.  It's easy for everyone.  Dealing with retards in your group is the only challenge at this point. <br /> <br />On difficult or new content the hardest part of the game is coordinating with your group and working as a team.  I submit that DPS are responsible for most of that coordination.  They are required to work with the other two DPS and the tank to prioritize kill targets, interrupt orders, CC etc...  Healing and tanking difficulty scale with the competency of your DPS. <br /> <br />A group with 3 strong, smart DPS will put most healers to sleep, and make tanks feel invincible.  A group with a bunch of goons behind their toons will make a healer feel helpless and frustrated and force tanks to play Arcane Mages for relief. <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />As far as DPS being spoiled by wrath, I think the problem is partly the random dungeon tool here.  You are dealing with randomly selected people who are incentivized to grind the sh*t out of old boring content for badges to get raid level gear.  They are not going to be all smiles and sunshine when their tank is actually looking to get drops from Heroic Nexus or w/e.  I think it's a design flaw that we have people with such large gear disparities running the same content. <br /> <br />When Cataclysm comes, at least initially, we'll all be starting from a gear reset and a clean slate.  Those DPS will be humbled and STFU.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Homer no function beer well without.</div></div>
