      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Borsuk wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">xorq wrote:</div><div class="orig"> I don't think DPS are the easiest classes to play. </div></div> <br /> <br /> <br />I won't waste your time and address all 4 points.  But speaking purely on the topic of heroics - Not raids where tiny differences in DPS performance can mean the difference between success and failure....  But speaking purely on the roll of DPS in Heroics... <br /> <br />If DPS isn't the easiest job - what is?   <br /> <br /></div></div> <br /> <br /><u>Assuming situations where you do not outgear the instances.</u> If you had 3 competent DPS which properly coordinate good use of interrupts, cc, defensive cooldowns and other miscellaneous abilities, tanking would be almost like melee DPS that doesn't need to avoid aggro or damage and healing would be something you can do completely ignoring everything around you except 5 hp bars and enemy aoe that you need to avoid. <br /> <br /><u>In the current wotlk heroics with grossly outgearing instances</u> tanking is only hard because DPS keep acting like aggrobots. <br /> <br />As for healing, it's a mix of extremes. The old heroics I do them in shadow spec with my priest, playing the role of DPS but queueing as healer for shorter queue. I only need to throw heals between pulls and at bosses, without even switching spec, and at many of the bosses I do not need to heal at all. But when you have DPSers that like to tank aggro and not use defensive cooldowns, certain parts of certain runs either become mission impossible or a lesson in Darwinism. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct  5th 2010  9:12pm by xorq </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>NOTE: I may post comments about my like/dislike/approval/disapproval of game features. <br />1- They are NOT a complaint. They are a perspective. <br />2- They are NOT advocacy. They are a perspective.</div></div>
