      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">xorq wrote:</div><div class="orig">I don't think DPS are the easiest classes to play. </div></div> <br /> <br />I do. <br /> <br />To counter your (xorq's) 4 points: <br /> <br /> <br />1): Avoiding Aggro and Damage Zones: Damage Zones are what everyone laughs at: &quot;Don't stand in the fire nub!&quot; Seriously, if moving out of Damage zones is that freaking hard, then we might as well fill dungeons and raids with level 1 mobs. The only time where this would ever become an issue, is if there's lag, and if there's that much lag, well... some nights are just not good dungeon/raid nights. As for reaching the aggro threshold, there's no excuse for this. The Built-In aggro meter works just fine; if you see orange around your nameplate and you're not the tank, STOP PRESSING BUTTONS (unless they are defensive or threat-reducing) and/or turn around, walk through the mob so your back is facing it, do whatever you have to do. It is an easy concept. <br /> <br />2): Even before Wrath came out with its stupidly easy dungeons, tanks/raid leaders have been marking Kill Orders way back in BC. I imagine they'll probably continue to do it even now. Is it that hard? &quot;Durrr Skull &gt; X &gt; Circle Durrrrr&quot; Also there's /assist tank. <br /> <br />3). Using interrupts is nothing new either. Of course, during Wrath, everybody was spoiled into the &quot;who cares just DPS it!&quot; I was never in that bunch myself, if I saw Shadow Blast in Old Kingdom for example, I interrupted it every damn time I saw it. If I saw a mob casting a heal, I interrupted it. I've always been doing this, and it is something that should be automatic to any good player. The bads will have to either shape up, or ship out. It isn't &quot;hard&quot;, per-se: Most of the &quot;MUST INTERRUPT THIS!&quot; moves/spells have a long casting timer, and or the boss freaking shouts what he's doing, and/or the game gives you RAID WARNINGS. What more do you want Blizz to do, make your character use said interrupts automatically so you don't have to? <br /> <br />4). Basically, you mean buffs, and debuffs, right? If that is &quot;Hard&quot; for a DPS to do, then I'm sorry... maybe they should go back to soloing. Buffs should be automatic; debuffs are usually hard-wired into the rotation, except for maybe things like Demo Shout. Not to mention many DPS' buffs/debuffs overlap anyways; Demo Shout and Vindication for example. <br /> <br />So no, I can't see where DPS have a more challenging time than Tanks and Healers. The challenge is, and has always been, Healer &gt; Tank &gt; DPS.</div>
